</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="11" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph box="[84,1357,2092,2186]" pageId="7" pageNumber="11" type="mainText">Ecology: Terrestrial and on rocks; in the Guianas rather common on white sand Savannas in xeromorphic scrub and light savanna forest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph box="[81,1356,2235,2425]" pageId="7" pageNumber="11" type="mainText">Note: Subsp. bartlettii was described for specimens with short and rigidly appressed leaves with excurrent (sometimes hyaline) costa (Florschütz 1964). Frahm considered this as a modification in drier habitats, since all possible intergradations occur (Frahm &amp; Gradstein 1987).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
